{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019pF8BYz1TN1ir6moUmUBrj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive report to the user.\n\n## Project Conventions Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and compiled comprehensive information about project conventions for implementing a new package. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. Module Path\n**Location:** `/workspace/go.mod`\n- **Module:** `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche`\n- **Go Version:** 1.25.3\n- **Key Dependencies:**\n  - `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1` (testing framework)\n  - `google.golang.org/grpc v1.79.1` (gRPC)\n  - `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.36.11` (Protocol Buffers)\n  - `modernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1` (SQLite driver)\n\n### 2. Domain.Run Type Definition\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Core Structure:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string\n    IsHost         bool\n    ParentRunID    string\n    TaskID         string\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName string) *Run` - Constructor\n- `Start()` - Transitions to running state\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName string)` - Track active step\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string)` - Complete a step\n- `Complete(state RunState)` - Mark run as completed\n- `Fail(msg string)` - Mark as failed\n- `FindFirstFailedStep() string` - Error recovery helper\n- `TaskAggregateStatus(runs []*Run) RunState` - Aggregate multiple runs\n\n### 3. Evolution Package Structure\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n\nThe evolution package is well-developed with 20 files total. Key files include:\n\n**Core Types & Data Flow:**\n- `types.go` - Central type definitions (`CollectedData`, `Lesson`, `EvolutionResult`, `Change`, `FitnessRecord`, `PopulationConfig`)\n- `fitness.go` - `FitnessRecord` and `CandidateFitness` structures with aggregation logic\n- `population.go` - `Population` type managing candidate prompt variants\n- `trigger.go` - `Trigger` type for debouncing evolution runs\n\n**Pipeline Stages (Orchestrated):**\n- `collector.go` - Collects runs and data\n- `classifier.go` - Classifies run outcomes\n- `reflector.go` - Extracts lessons from failures\n- `curator.go` - Curates knowledge base\n- `scriptgen.go` - Generates evolution scripts\n- `orchestrator.go` - Wires all stages together\n\n**Supporting Components:**\n- `selector.go` - Selects among candidates\n- `audit.go` - Logs evolution changes\n- `llmclient.go` - LLM abstraction interface\n- `corruption_test.go` - Data integrity testing\n\n**Disk Layout Pattern:**\n```\n.cloche/evolution/\n  population/<step-name>/\n    candidate-001.md\n    candidate-002.md\n    meta.jsonl\n    assignments.jsonl\n  fitness/<workflow>.jsonl\n  snapshots/\n```\n\n### 4. Testing Conventions\n\n**Pattern (from 40+ test files examined):**\n\n**Test Package Naming:**\n- Located alongside main code with `_test.go` suffix\n- Package: `<package>_test` (e.g., `domain_test`, `evolution_test`)\n\n**Testing Structure:**\n- Uses `github.com/stretchr/testify` for assertions\n- Three main assertion styles:\n  - `assert.*` - Non-fatal failures (continue testing)\n  - `require.*` - Fatal failures (stop test)\n  - Table-driven tests with `struct` and `for _, tt := range tests`\n\n**Example Pattern:**\n```go\npackage domain_test\n\nimport (\n    \"testing\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n)\n\nfunc TestRunLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n    run := domain.NewRun(\"run-1\", \"test-workflow\")\n    assert.Equal(t, domain.RunStatePending, run.State)\n    \n    run.Start()\n    assert.Equal(t, domain.RunStateRunning, run.State)\n}\n\nfunc TestTableDriven(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name string\n        in   string\n        want string\n    }{\n        {\"case 1\", \"input\", \"expected\"},\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            assert.Equal(t, tt.want, someFunc(tt.in))\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Helper Patterns:**\n- Local helper functions marked with `t.Helper()`\n- Temp directories for file tests: `t.TempDir()`\n- Database testing with in-memory SQLite: `sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")`\n\n**Test Coverage Examples:**\n- Constructor and lifecycle methods\n- State transitions\n- Error conditions\n- Data persistence (with `require` for setup)\n- Concurrent/synchronization scenarios\n- Integration tests with full chains\n\n### 5. Package Structure & Organization\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture Pattern:**\n```\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Pure domain types (Run, Workflow, Step, etc.)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (RunStore, ContainerRuntime, etc.)\n  adapters/         # Implementations\n    docker/         # Docker runtime\n    sqlite/         # SQLite store\n    grpc/           # gRPC server/client\n    agents/         # Agent adapters\n    web/            # Web handler\n    local/          # Local runtime\n  evolution/        # Self-evolving pipeline\n  dsl/              # Workflow DSL parser/mutator\n  engine/           # Execution engine\n  host/             # Host-side workflow executor\n  agent/            # In-container agent\n  config/           # Configuration\n  version/          # Version management\n  logstream/        # Log streaming\n  protocol/         # Protocol definitions\n  runcontext/       # Run context management\n```\n\n**Key Design Principles Evident:**\n- **Dependency Injection** - Types receive dependencies in constructors\n- **Interface-based** - All I/O and external services via interfaces (ports)\n- **Context-aware** - Functions use `context.Context` for cancellation/timeouts\n- **Error Handling** - Explicit error returns with `fmt.Errorf` wrapping\n- **No globals** - Configuration passed through structs\n- **JSONL for persistence** - Human-readable, append-only log format\n\n### 6. File Paths Summary\n\n**Key Files Read:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Core Run type\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go` - Run type tests\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` - Evolution types\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness_test.go` - Fitness testing\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/population_test.go` - Population tests\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness.go` - Fitness implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/population.go` - Population implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go` - SQLite test patterns\n- `/workspace/go.mod` - Module definition\n\n**Evolution Package Files (all in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`):**\n`orchestrator.go`, `classifier.go`, `reflector.go`, `curator.go`, `scriptgen.go`, `trigger.go`, `fitness.go`, `population.go`, `selector.go`, `audit.go`, `collector.go`, `llmclient.go`, `types.go`, plus corresponding `_test.go` files"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abfc295a10636b302 (use SendMessage with to: 'abfc295a10636b302' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36900\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 32705</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6717437-3589-4939-a51b-a20f6016956f","uui